ENTRY       EC 1.8.7.2                  Enzyme
NAME        ferredoxin:thioredoxin reductase
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on a sulfur group of donors;
            With an iron-sulfur protein as acceptor
SYSNAME     ferredoxin:thioredoxin disulfide oxidoreductase
REACTION    2 reduced ferredoxin + thioredoxin disulfide = 2 oxidized ferredoxin + thioredoxin + 2 H+ [RN:R09502]
ALL_REAC    R09502
SUBSTRATE   reduced ferredoxin [CPD:C00138];
            thioredoxin disulfide [CPD:C00343]
PRODUCT     oxidized ferredoxin [CPD:C00139];
            thioredoxin [CPD:C00342];
            H+ [CPD:C00080]
COMMENT     The enzyme contains a [4Fe-4S] cluster and internal disulfide. It forms a mixed disulfide with thioredoxin on one side, and docks ferredoxin on the other side, enabling two one-electron transfers. The reduced thioredoxins generated by the enzyme activate the Calvin cycle enzymes EC 3.1.3.11 (fructose-bisphosphatase), EC 3.1.3.37
            (sedoheptulose-bisphosphatase) and EC 2.7.1.19 (phosphoribulokinase) as well as other chloroplast enzymes by disulfide reduction.
HISTORY     EC 1.8.7.2 created 2010
